I don't have the approach of,
okay, let's take the money,

11:11.360 --> 11:13.130 align:middle line:84%
go hire a bunch of
people, get an office,

11:13.130 --> 11:14.270 align:middle line:90%
all that-- not that at all.

11:14.270 --> 11:16.130 align:middle line:84%
It's, I'm going
to figure it out.

11:16.130 --> 11:17.430 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you an example.

11:17.430 --> 11:20.810 align:middle line:84%
If advertising online is
critical to the growth

11:20.810 --> 11:23.240 align:middle line:84%
of your business,
you have to learn it,

11:23.240 --> 11:25.130 align:middle line:90%
and I'm going to tell you why.

11:25.130 --> 11:29.827 align:middle line:84%
In a digital world, where we're
buying and selling ads online,

11:29.827 --> 11:31.160 align:middle line:90%
the company you're buying from--

11:31.160 --> 11:33.050 align:middle line:84%
Google, Facebook,
whatever it may be--

11:33.050 --> 11:35.810 align:middle line:84%
they're continuously
adjusting their algorithms.

11:35.810 --> 11:37.910 align:middle line:84%
They're continuously
changing because they're

11:37.910 --> 11:40.410 align:middle line:84%
trying to maximize
their returns as well.

11:40.410 --> 11:42.980 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a
never-ending battle--

11:42.980 --> 11:45.380 align:middle line:84%
and I truly mean
the word, "battle--"

11:45.380 --> 11:47.690 align:middle line:84%
to see-- they're trying to
see how much of your money

11:47.690 --> 11:50.690 align:middle line:84%
they can get for every
ad that they sell,

11:50.690 --> 11:52.880 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying to
see how many sales you

11:52.880 --> 11:57.440 align:middle line:84%
get for every ad you buy and
trying to make that profitable.

11:57.440 --> 12:00.590 align:middle line:84%
So there's a constant push-pull
that's forever changing.

12:00.590 --> 12:02.960 align:middle line:84%
Part of the
challenges you have--

12:02.960 --> 12:07.330 align:middle line:84%
and this applies to every
company I've ever invested in--

12:07.330 --> 12:09.940 align:middle line:84%
because it's not
easy to understand

12:09.940 --> 12:12.100 align:middle line:84%
how all those
algorithms break down,

12:12.100 --> 12:14.440 align:middle line:84%
we tend to go out
there and hire people.

12:14.440 --> 12:15.910 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not going
to say that's bad

12:15.910 --> 12:18.310 align:middle line:84%
all the time because it's
hard to learn that stuff,

12:18.310 --> 12:22.000 align:middle line:84%
